1
00:01:15,280 --> 00:01:19,120
1099 A.D. It was an age
of religious Crusades and Holy Wars.

2
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:22,960
After a grueling
four-year campaign...

3
00:01:22,960 --> 00:01:25,840
the Knights of Christendom finally
arrived at the gates of Jerusalem.

4
00:01:25,840 --> 00:01:28,720
During the furious battle
for the Holy City...

5
00:01:28,720 --> 00:01:31,600
a Flemish Knight,
Charles Le Vaillant...

6
00:01:31,600 --> 00:01:35,440
had a life-changing epiphany.

7
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:16,720
Le Vaillant was struck
by the hypocrisy of killing...

8
00:02:16,720 --> 00:02:20,560
fellow human beings
in the name of religion...

9
00:02:20,560 --> 00:02:24,400
especially since these people
professed belief in the same god.

10
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:27,280
The Fazar,
Le Vaillant's written account...

11
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:29,200
of his experiences
in the Holy Land...

12
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:32,080
tells us he wandered the streets
of conquered Jerusalem...

13
00:02:32,080 --> 00:02:35,920
for days after that bloody battle...

14
00:02:35,920 --> 00:02:38,800
until he found the entrance
of a cave...

15
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:41,680
that ran beneath the length
of the Holy City.

16
00:02:41,680 --> 00:02:45,520
Inside that cave, he began
to record his epiphany...

17
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:48,400
which became the basis
for a new religious sect...

18
00:02:48,400 --> 00:02:51,280
an order that would combine
the fundamental tenets...

19
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:54,160
of the three major religious
of his day.

20
00:02:54,160 --> 00:02:57,040
His first converts were
fellow Christian knights...

21
00:02:57,040 --> 00:03:00,880
who'd also become disenchanted
by the bloodshed.

22
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:03,760
The force of his convictions
even won over...

23
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:07,600
a number of Muslims and Jews,
former enemies...

24
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:11,440
who now became willing converts
to the new faith.

25
00:03:11,440 --> 00:03:14,320
Many years after completing
the original Fazar...

26
00:03:14,320 --> 00:03:17,200
Le Vaillant had further revelations.

27
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:21,040
He wrote these down, intending them
to be added as the final chapter.

28
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:24,880
Around the same time,
he and his followers...

29
00:03:24,880 --> 00:03:28,720
were being accused of heresy
by the Crusader authorities.

30
00:03:28,720 --> 00:03:31,600
On their way to Syria,
he and a group of disciples...

31
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:35,440
were intercepted by some
of the very same Crusaders...

32
00:03:35,440 --> 00:03:39,280
he had once commanded.

33
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:12,880
During the battle that followed...

34
